property.name: text
property.value:
This model provides a web service that takes setpoints, runs a simulation model of a simple HVAC system, and estimates the cost of the setpoints.
To access the web service, run the model, then point your browser to:
http://localhost:8078/start
or double click on this comment.

property.name: text
property.value:
Users can specify four parameters in the web page: TDay: desired temperature during the day in celsius TNight: desired temperature during the night in celsius LTime: time to leave home for work ([0, 24]) RTime: time to return home from work ([0, 24])
During [LTime, RTime], the heater will be turned off no matter what the temperature is to save energy. It will be turned on one hour before RTime to warm up the room so that it will not be too cold inside when the user returns home.
If LTime >= RTime, they are both ignored.

svg.text:
This model illustrates the implementation of a room model and a proportional controller.
Input to the room model is the control signal u_k. Output of the room model is the new room temperature T_{k+1}.
The room model and the control action is computed in Ptolemy II.
Author: Michael Wetter Modified by Baobing (Brian) Wang

Cost model: OFF: no cost WARM: $0.002/min HEAT: $0.004/min "unitCost" is updated by the state machine. This model simulates the room for two days. Thus, the cost is multiplied by 15 to get monthly cost.
